{% set agent_style_voice_chat = GetCustomerAttribute(field="project_representative_agent_style") %}

{% if not agent_style_voice_chat.strip() %}
    {{Return()}}
{% endif %}

{{DeleteCustomerAttribute(field="project_representative_agent_style")}}

{% set agent_style_voice_chat = agent_style_voice_chat[0].upper() ~ agent_style_voice_chat[1:] %}
{% if not agent_style_voice_chat.endswith(".") %}
    {% set agent_style_voice_chat = agent_style_voice_chat ~ "." %}
{% endif %}

{# Move all previous instructions regarding tone of voice as is to new voice speaking style attribute. #}
{{SetCustomerAttribute(field="project_representative_agent_voice_speaking_style", value=agent_style_voice_chat)}}

{% set schema = {
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "overall_tone": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Persona and interpersonal style that should apply to both chat and voice: e.g., friendly, confident, professional, humorous, light-hearted, empathetic. Focus on who the assistant feels like and how they relate to the user, not on pacing, breathing, accent, or other delivery mechanics. Can reuse or lightly rephrase key sentences from the input."
    },
    "speech_delivery": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "All instructions that affect spoken delivery: pacing, tempo, rhythm, pauses, breathing, fillers, acknowledgements, intonation, pitch, prosody, accent, channel-specific rules, and other voice-only behavior. May include persona sentences if they describe how the voice should sound. Usually contains most or all of the original instruction text."
    }
  },
  "required": ["overall_tone", "speech_delivery"]
} %}


{% set prompt %}You are given a block of instructions describing how an AI voice should sound.

Split this text into exactly TWO fields in JSON:

1. "overall_tone"
2. "speech_delivery"

Use these rules:

- "overall_tone":
  - Contains persona and interpersonal style that should apply to BOTH chat and voice.
  - Include traits like: friendly, confident, professional, warm, calm, light-hearted, humorous, empathetic, not pushy, direct and concise, etc.
  - Also include “who you are” descriptions, such as “like a friendly, experienced professional” or “like a real secretary”.
  - You may copy 1–3 key sentences or phrases from the input that best describe the assistant’s character and how they emotionally relate to the user.
  - Do NOT include technical voice mechanics: no speech tempo details, no pitch ranges, no breathing, no fillers, no prosody numbers.

- "speech_delivery":
  - Contains ALL instructions about how speech is produced in voice:
    - pace, tempo, rhythm, breathing, pauses, micro-pauses
    - intonation, pitch, prosody, semitone ranges
    - accents and language variants
    - fillers, acknowledgement phrases, discourse markers
    - channel-specific or phone-specific rules
    - constraints such as avoiding sounding scripted or avoiding certain slang.
  - You may include persona sentences here as well if they describe how the voice should sound.
  - In general, keep most or all of the original instructions in this field, preserving wording when possible.

Additional rules:
- If the input only contains voice mechanics (e.g., pace, accent) and no persona or interpersonal tone, set "overall_tone" to an empty string.
- Avoid turning "overall_tone" into a long list of adjectives separated by commas; prefer short phrases or sentences instead.

Instructions:
{{agent_style_voice_chat}}{% endset %}

{# Optimization: no need to call LLM for default cases #}
{% if (agent_style_voice_chat.strip().lower() == "friendly professional, super welcoming. speak energetic and fast") or (agent_style_voice_chat.strip().lower() == "friendly professional, super welcoming. speak energetic and fast.") %}
    {% set result_json = {
      "overall_tone": "Friendly professional, super welcoming."
    } %}
{% else %}
    {% set result_json = json.loads(utils_structured_generation(schema=schema, prompt=prompt)) %}
{% endif %}

{% set overall_tone = result_json.overall_tone %}

{% if overall_tone.strip() %}
    {% set chat_style = result_json.overall_tone[0].upper() ~ result_json.overall_tone[1:] %}
    {% if not chat_style.endswith(".") %}
        {% set chat_style = chat_style ~ "." %}
    {% endif %}
{% else %}
    {% set chat_style = "" %}
{% endif %}

{{SetCustomerAttribute(field="project_representative_agent_chat_speaking_style", value=chat_style)}}
